This paper deals with dynamic connectivity, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. The paper presents a new randomized dynamic connectivity structure with improved update and query times. This topic falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). The paper also involves analyzing the performance of the structure, which could fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses probabilistic techniques, which could fall under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
